The paper deals with description logics, which are a subfield of artificial intelligence and knowledge representation. The focus is on model theory and logical reasoning, which are topics that fall under the category of logic (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the use of DLs for computer aided processing of knowledge, which is relevant to databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the expressiveness of DLs and their application to modal logics, which are topics that fall under natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper presents algorithms for deciding the L1-to-L2-rewritability problem, which is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG).
